com.bluegosling.apt.reflect

Class ArParameter<M extends ArExecutableMember>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bluegosling.apt.reflect.ArParameter<M>
  • Type Parameters:
    M - the type of executable member (constructor or method) to which the parameter belongs
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ArAnnotatedConstruct, ArAnnotatedElement

    public class ArParameter<M extends ArExecutableMember>
extends Object
    A representation of a parameter to an executable member, like a constructor or method. This is analogous to Parameter, except that it represents parameters in Java source (during annotation processing) vs. representing parameters in runtime types.

    Unlike reflection-based parameters, there is no way to determine if the parameter name is synthesized. For types whose source code is being processed, the names are always available. But, for elements that represent types on the compiler's class path, parameter names may not be available and instead be synthesized.

    See Also:
    Parameter, VariableElement
